<paragraph id="293F36DCFFFEB964758A3278303F987B" blockId="3.[151,424,1311,1372]" box="[151,282,1346,1372]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
<figureCitation id="B1BB2A59FFFEB964758A3278303F987B" box="[151,282,1346,1372]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 27" captionStartId="4.[151,257,1920,1941]" captionTargetBox="[195,1389,191,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[163,1423,178,1932]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 27. Bhatia serrata sp. nov. 14. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 15. Head and thorax, profile; 16. Face; 17. Forewing; 18. Male genital capsule, lateral view; 19. Subgenital plate, dorsal view; 20. Male style, dorsal view; 21. Connective, ventral view; 22. Aedeagus, lateral view; 23. Aedeagus, caudal view; 24. Apex of aedeagal shaft and ventral process, cephalic view; 25. Female seventh sternite, ventral view; 26. Second pair of valvula, left lateral view; 27. Magnified view of second pair of valvula, left lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190680/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
Figs 
<number id="9F4824FBFFFEB96475CC3278303F987B" box="[209,282,1346,1372]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="20.5" valueMax="27.0" valueMin="14.0">14–27</number>
</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="619A6557FFFEB962758A32AA33439C01" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="52" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" type="description">
<paragraph id="293F36DCFFFEB964758A32AA345B9BB5" blockId="3.[151,1437,1424,2030]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
Chocolate brown. Face pale brown with dark brown markings as shown in figure 
<number id="9F4824FBFFFEB964714132AA3559988D" box="[1116,1148,1424,1450]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="16.0">16</number>
. Vertex pale brown with transverse arcuate dark brown band across ocelli and more posterior band often interrupted at places across eyes; 
<number id="9F4824FBFFFEB96475C332E7302E98D0" box="[222,267,1501,1527]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
spots mesad of eye behind band dark brown. Pronoutm pale brown with connected dark brown maculae surrounding paler spots (in some specimens maculae coalesce to form irregular spot near hind margin). Scutellum brown with dark brown connected maculae surrounding paler areas in median area and bordering scutellar triangles. Fore and hind wings uniformly chocolate brown, venation slightly darker, apices of claval veins, costal margin and apical region darker. Female seventh sternite medially darkly pigmented.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="293F36DCFFFEB96475DB31A432169A21" blockId="3.[151,1437,1424,2030]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
Head declivous anteriorly smoothly curving to face, vertex shorter at middle than next to eye. Face in profile convex, shagreen. Ocelli placed 
<number id="9F4824FBFFFEB964776431FF33AD9BF8" box="[633,648,1733,1759]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="3.0">3</number>
times own diameter away from adjacent eye. Pronoutm gibbous. 
<collectingCountry id="5197764CFFFEB964758A31D631F79A21" box="[151,210,1772,1798]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Hind</collectingCountry>
basitarsus with 
<number id="9F4824FBFFFEB964749231D630BB9A21" box="[399,414,1772,1798]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="4.0">4</number>
platellae on apical transverse row.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="293F36DCFFFEB96475DB302935779AC9" blockId="3.[151,1437,1424,2030]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="1BF4EACEFFFEB96475DB302930579A0B" box="[198,370,1811,1836]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: Pygophore without oblique ridge or processes, caudo-dorsal angle conical, ventral margin rounded. Subgenital plate dorsally upcurved in distal half, with short slender setae on outer margin more numerous in basal half than in distal half. Style with well developed preapical lobe, apophysis with lateral, beak-like projection, surface rugose. Aedeagus with paired ventral process from long preatrium, each process slender and oppressed to each other; dorsal apodeme well developed; shaft curved dorsally, half length of ventral processes, laterally serrated with subapical gonopore on posterior surface.
</paragraph>
<caption id="7DFF6654FFF9B963758A30BA34559AC9" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190680/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" targetBox="[195,1389,191,1903]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="293F36DCFFF9B963758A30BA34559AC9" blockId="4.[151,1437,1920,2030]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="1BF4EACEFFF9B963758A30BA330B9AB2" bold="true" box="[151,558,1920,1942]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">
FIGURES 14–27. 
<taxonomicName id="EE804D5FFFF9B963745330BB30FE9AB1" box="[334,475,1921,1942]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bhatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="1BF4EACEFFF9B963745330BB30FE9AB1" bold="true" box="[334,475,1921,1942]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Bhatia serrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="00C757B5FFF9B96374FC30BA330B9AB2" box="[481,558,1920,1941]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
14. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 15. Head and thorax, profile; 16. Face; 17. Forewing; 18. Male genital capsule, lateral view; 19. Subgenital plate, dorsal view; 20. Male style, dorsal view; 21. Connective, ventral view; 22. Aedeagus, lateral view; 23. Aedeagus, caudal view; 24. Apex of aedeagal shaft and ventral process, cephalic view; 25. Female seventh sternite, ventral view; 26. Second pair of valvula, left lateral view; 27. Magnified view of second pair of valvula, left lateral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="293F36DCFFF8B96275DB37A2353A9DFF" blockId="5.[151,1436,152,567]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="1BF4EACEFFF8B96275DB37A230A89D96" box="[198,397,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Female genitalia</emphasis>
: Seventh sternite with V-shaped excavation on hind margin. Second pair of valvula with smooth margined teeth, distal cutting edge occupying about 
<number id="9F4824FBFFF8B9627644378432A89DFF" box="[857,909,190,216]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="0.47">0.47</number>
of valvulae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="293F36DCFFF8B96275DB37DF33439C01" blockId="5.[151,1436,152,567]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="1BF4EACEFFF8B96275DB37DF30559DD9" box="[198,368,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Measurements</emphasis>
: Male 
<number id="9F4824FBFFF8B96274DE37DF30C29DD8" box="[451,487,229,255]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="7.4">7.4</number>
(
<number id="9F4824FBFFF8B96274EB37DF33749DD8" box="[502,593,229,255]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="7.45" valueMax="7.5" valueMin="7.4">7.4–7.5</number>
) mm long and 
<number id="9F4824FBFFF8B962761F37DF32039DD8" box="[770,806,229,255]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="2.6">2.6</number>
(
<number id="9F4824FBFFF8B962762B37DF32B49DD8" box="[822,913,229,255]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="2.6" valueMax="2.7" valueMin="2.5">2.5–2.7</number>
) mm wide across eyes. Female 
<number id="9F4824FBFFF8B962701837DF340F9DD8" box="[1285,1322,229,255]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="8.9">8.9</number>
(
<number id="9F4824FBFFF8B962702537DF34789DD8" box="[1336,1373,229,255]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" value="8.8">8.8</number>
–9.0) mm long and 
<quantity id="EE789B39FFF8B9627424363630B69C01" box="[313,403,268,294]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" unit="mm" value="3.1">3.1 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
