<subSubSection id="619A6557FFF8B96275DB369334079F10" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="293F36DCFFF8B96275DB369334079F10" blockId="5.[151,1436,152,567]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="1BF4EACEFFF8B96275DB3693301D9CE4" bold="true" box="[198,312,425,451]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="EE804D5FFFF8B962745A369330D59CE5" box="[327,496,425,450]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bhatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serrata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="1BF4EACEFFF8B962745A369330D59CE5" box="[327,496,425,450]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Bhatia serrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="00C757B5FFF8B96274E5369333779CE4" box="[504,594,425,451]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="EE804D5FFFF8B96277C8369332C39CE4" authority="Metcalf" authorityName="Metcalf" box="[725,998,425,451]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bhatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guamensis">
<emphasis id="1BF4EACEFFF8B96277C8369332549CE5" box="[725,881,425,450]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">B. guamensis</emphasis>
(Metcalf)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="5197764CFFF8B9627130369335509CE4" box="[1069,1141,425,451]" name="Guam" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Guam</collectingCountry>
in head shape and shares the lateral serrated aedeagus with 
<taxonomicName id="EE804D5FFFF8B962773E36EA32679CCD" authority="Kwon &amp; Lee" authorityName="Kwon &amp; Lee" box="[547,834,464,490]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bhatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="koreana">
<emphasis id="1BF4EACEFFF8B962773E36EA33879CCE" box="[547,674,464,489]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">B. koreana</emphasis>
Kwon &amp; Lee
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="5197764CFFF8B962769436EA32F59CCD" box="[905,976,464,490]" name="South Korea" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Korea</collectingCountry>
but differs from both species in having an elongate preatrium and the ventral processes oppressed to each other. The new species shares the structure of style with 
<taxonomicName id="EE804D5FFFF8B962742C352433589F10" authority="Matsumura" authorityName="Matsumura" box="[305,637,541,567]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bhatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="satsumensis">
<emphasis id="1BF4EACEFFF8B962742C352430F89F10" box="[305,477,542,567]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">B. satsumensis</emphasis>
(Matsumura)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="5197764CFFF8B96277D83527322D9F10" box="[709,776,541,567]" name="Japan" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Japan</collectingCountry>
but lacks the subapical processes to the shaft.
</paragraph>
